The paper deals with the optimization of reserve prices in single item auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of data and simulations, which suggests that it could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of optimizing reserve prices, which could place it in the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the economic implications of reserve prices, which could place it in the category of economics and computation (cs.EC).
